                            <comment id="468871" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2025 06:00:05 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alex Zhuravlev, do we really need to have extents on the MDT to do the batch preallocation? I recall that there was an option in the past to preallocate directory blocks for improved performance, and that definitely existed long before mballoc and extents were added.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I checked that again: with extents disabled we have 0-2 multi-block allocations from ~400 blocks allocated (in benchmark), with extents enabled  ~96 multi-block allocations and very few single-block allocations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
